OL,6,FThe court heard Emma Martin had been
OL,7,Fasleep and woke to the sounds of the
OL,8,Fletterbox snapping shut before she
OL,9,Fheard the "crackling sounds" of a fire.
OL,11,F"She got up and went to the front door
OL,12,Fand could see orange flames from the
OL,13,Fletterbox beginning to grow quickly,"
OL,14,Fthe court was told.
OL,16,FSmoke began to develop making it
OL,17,Fdifficult for her to breathe. She
OL,18,Fattempted to save her cat, which was
OL,19,Fdownstairs and in 'distress', but the
OL,20,Fextent of the smoke forced her to flee
OL,21,Fupstairs.
